I got my 9th ring today so I thought I'd share.<br>
<br>
First, you must be dubious or better to Dain Frostreaver IV faction to do the quest....it's possible to do it kos if you can sneak, but I'm not gonna go into how that works now.<br>
<br>
Seneshcal Aldikar in icewell keep can be found in two different places: At night he's in his room on the middle floor...hard to explain where but you dont' need him there anyway. at around 9am he respawns in the room up top next to Dain's throne, and shouts that the Royal court is now in session or something.<br>
<br>
Give him the 8th ring (optional - won't give you anything but a dialogue). you'll get it back. Now tell him: 'i will accept the task', and he gives you a 6-slot container (traitor's bane box). you need 6 items, dropped off various traitor dorfs. they all con dubious and have no faction hit.<br>
<br>
* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Dirk of the Traitor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> drops off Rodrick in EW. he spawns right at the zone out from crystal caverns at approx loc -3300, +1100. he's like lvl 35 very easy kill. you should have his dagger from when you did the 6th ring, in where his head is needed. he's a pretty damn rare spawn, some people have camped him for up to 10 hours. he should spawn when 'a Rygorr Emissary' spawns at the exit of CC, and if left unaggroed it will result in Rodrick popping.<br>
<br>
* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Murdrick's Head</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in GD, Murdrick Tardok spawns in a cave along with 5-6 other dwarves. The loc of the entrance to the cave is approximately -5500, +3200, it's up on the hill on the cliffside. walk into the cave and in the first room on the right is the cave. now wait for him to start his dialogue. this might take a while I'm not sure excactly how much after he spawns. as soon as he starts talking to the other dorfs, have a druid or ranger harmony all the dorfs in the cave, and a lvl 60 single pull him out thru the cave. kill him, he's about lvl 50 (doesn't summon) and not hard. totally resistant to spells.<br>
<br>
should have a short respawn time about 30 mins<br>
<br>
* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Berradin's Head</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> make tainted avalache ale, a brew that's trivial at skill 248. I got 195 skill and am 2/4 so far for successes/attempts. combine this:<br>
<br>
- a bottle (merchant)<br>
- iceball (off dervishes in EW, approx 10% drop rate)<br>
- ice wyvern stinger (off wyverns in CS, approx 10% drop rate - no drop)<br>
- arctic mussels (foraged in velious, spawns on the seafloor in CS a lot too)<br>
- seahorse scales (off seahorses in SG and Kedge, drop by the bucketload)<br>
- Runed sea shell with 1 charge of 'Cloud' (rather rare off sirens in the underground cave in SG)<br>
- Mind melt (poison made by a rogue...not trivial at 250 but doable)<br>
<br>
give the tainted avalanche ale to Captain Berradin in EW. he's in a hut at approx loc 0, +2400. he says thanks for the ale, drinks it, and after about 30 seconds he starts shaking violently. he will respawn and fall to the ground (like he was dead). kill the respawned version, the other dorfs don't assist. he's pretty easy around lvl 40-42 (can be assassinated <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     ). loot head and note to peffin. practically always up.<br>
<br>
* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Peffin's Head</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the frost giant fort in EW, there is an invisible female dorf named Peffin Ambersnow. she stands inside the right hut inside the fort, along with some giants. clear the fort of giants, and have your friends ready at the wall of the fort, opposite of the gate. give the Note to her, and 3 kromrif elite will spawn inside her hut. bring them to the party and kill them. they're lvl 51 (summon), with 15k HP i estimate, kinda rough. quite resistant but slowable.<br>
<br>
now, 5 more kromrif elite will spawn in front of the fire in the middle of the fort. peffin will run to them and they will form a circle around her. the special thing about these kromrif elite is that they can't move. they're not rooted, they just dont move. hence, they will agro the one with most agro, use that to your advantadge. have an enchanter or shaman chain cast tash or slow or some high agro slow on them, and you can fight peffin safely while the giants do nothing. peffin also cannot move, so you gotta fight her at her spawn point. she shoots arrows at people :P<br>
<br>
Peffin will NOT resist lures as lately rumoured. a 57 wizard landed 7 out of 9 lures on her. so alternatively you can bring a few wizard friends to nuke her to hell. run in quick and loot her then move out.<br>
<br>
you can also try using harmony so you can fight peffin safely. not sure if this will work but worth a shot<br>
<br>
I had about 12 people for this, including 60 war, 3 clerics, 60 shaman and assorted melee / druids. I suggest bringing 2 clerics and a shaman to debuff. and the appropriate amount of classes if you wanna try either the agro-method, lure nuking or harmony. I would recommend the Lure method, it seems pretty safe.<br>
<br>
there is a problem here by the way - with more and more people doing the quest, sometimes people will just leave the 5 giants up. when I did my ring about 20 giants were up, making the whole deal a lot harder. but a mix of agroing, harmonying and lure nuking seemed to work well.<br>
<br>
also, dont have DAMAGE SHIELDS up or you might do enough damage to giants hitting people and they will start summoning you.<br>
<br>
loot her head, note, and the bow she drops (decent bow, 25/50 and stats. tradable). peffin has about 20-30 min respawn time.<br>
<br>
* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Doldigun's Head</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Go to the 'manor' area in Kael. when coming from EW thru kael, you'll notice this huge ice cave on the left side with a lot of giants standing - walk up the ramp and into the house you find. i suggest bringing two good groups for this, near 60. if you have lvl 50-55 people bring 3 groups. now, start clearing the house and move in. get to the throne room, huge room with a lot of giants, and start pulling / clearing the room. when it's clear, walk to the throne and say this, while standing on top of the throne:<br>
<br>
The Dain shall be slain for the peace we must obtain<br>
<br>
Doldigun, dubious dorf, will now spawn. Give him the note from Peffin and you will receive a ring (councelor's ring or something). attack him and he poofs. run back to the stairs where your party should be, and giants will start spawning and come towards you, one by one. they get harder and harder, the last one is lvl 60, hits for low 200's and has maybe 50k hp. not as hard as you might think really just make sure you have enough healers and mana when you start.<br>
<br>
keep killing until the last one is dead and Doldigun respawns. he will try to run from the throne and up the stairs, attack him asap and kill him. approx lvl 50 hits for like 150, 10k hp not hard at all. loot his head. he should practically always be up, might be a limit on how often you can spawn him but I don't know.<br>
<br>
* <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Juliah's Head</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in icewell keep, go over the bridge, past the pit area, and into the small arena where a dorf is asleep on the seats and 3 dorfs are standing in a triangle like they're discussing. give Councelor Juliah Lockheart the ring you got from doldigun, and she will respawn, kos to all. hits for 350 double, has about 15k hp I estimate. immune to slow, resistant. other dorfs will not assist her. loot her head. fast respawn I think, guessing 30 mins an hour tops.<br>
<br>
Now combine the dagger and 5 heads you got in the traitor's bane box from the seneschal and you get a new box (box of trust or something). give this combined box and your 8th ring to DAIN FROSTREAVER IV, NOT THE SENESHCAL! he gives you the 9th ring.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://prod.homepage.dk/pics/9thring.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
now, I know this walthrough is kinda messy, but I wanted to focus mostly on how hard the mobs are and what kinda force you need for it.<br>
<br>
